Here's a comprehensive summary of the project:

Project: HW4 - Context Compaction for NanoCLI (CS598-LMZ, Spring 2026)
What It Does
This is an academic assignment that extends a minimal coding agent (nanocli) with automatic context compaction. When a long conversation with an LLM exceeds a configured token limit, the agent:

Sends a summarization prompt to the model
Replaces the entire conversation history with a single compact checkpoint message
Continues the task seamlessly from the compacted state
The goal is to enable agents to survive long-horizon coding tasks without hitting context window limits.

