run_turn
This is a Python generator (yield/send) that drives the tool-calling loop. Key design points:

Compaction before every model request — maybe_compact_session is called at the top of each iteration. On the first iteration it runs before the new user message is appended, so a compaction won't erase the current request.
session.stream_response_final() — the existing method that calls the OpenAI Responses API and returns (list[ChatItem], total_tokens). The token count is stored back onto the session so the next iteration's compaction check has up-to-date data.
Per-item yielding — Messages and ToolCallInputs are yielded in the order they appear in the response. For each tool call, a ToolApprovalRequest is yielded next (unless session.yolo or the tool is read-only); the approval boolean comes back via generator.send(). The result is always yielded as a ToolCallOutput and appended to session.context so the next API call sees it.
Loop termination — if a response contains no tool calls, the loop ends.
